<TEXT>
the anchorman doesnt look like peter dan or 
tom and doesnt use a teleprompter he looks at the camera and says 
something in russian welcome comrades says the translators 
voiceover 
vremya the soviet evening news program has come to us 
public television more than 100 public broadcasting service 
stations from new york to los angeles are broadcasting vremya 
in a twoweek test begun feb 12 and coordinated by bostons wgbh 
vremya it means time in russian has telegenic 
anchors marina burtseva and kira grigoryeva but lacks the pinball 
graphics and slick electronic packaging of us network news 
grigoryeva sits in front of the logo burtseva before a shelf of 
casually toppled videotape cases they read from their scripts 
glasnost is evident in its workmanlike sovietseye view of the 
upheavals of soviet society in transition such as the ethnic riots 
by hooliganist thugs in tadzhikistan and corruption in labor 
unions 
its like a broadcast you might have found in the 1960s 
said steven weinstock executive producer of the eleventh hour 
late news show on the new york city pbs station wnet his station 
broadcasts vremya at 130 am 
while technically primitive vremya is straightforward in 
presenting the news he said it lacks the entertainment values 
that have crept into us news and it lacks the technical wizardry 
and its refreshing 
it also allows an american audience to see the most popular 
broadcast in the soviet union to see what is driving soviet public 
opinion and get a good sense of what is going on he said 
it has been estimated that 150 million soviet people watch the 9 
pm moscow edition of vremya which would make it the most 
popular tv broadcast in the world if only the soviets had ac 
nielsen co 
in the united states nine of the nations top 10 public tv 
stations are airing vremya said wgbh news director alan 
foster the broadcasters are seeking underwriters for the show 
which foster estimates would cost 1 million a year 
other bigmarket stations participating include los angeles new 
york city san francisco seattle denver chicago minneapolis 
st louis new orleans dallas and washington 
theres not a lot in the deep south and not much of the 
southwest although lubbock texas and las cruces nm are 
running it foster said but otherwise the heartland of america 
has really taken to it as has the big city 
were very excited about it said stella giammasi 
spokeswoman for wnet she said wnet got the show on short notice 
and could schedule it for only 130 am if the experiment 
succeeds wnet could put vremya in prime time 
boston viewers see the show at 430 pm and chicago viewers 
watch it at 1030 pm it even penetrated commercial tv when the 
philadelphia pbs station opted not to use it and wtgi an 
international format uhf station grabbed it instead 
wgbh which solicits viewer mail at the end of the halfhour 
broadcast by friday had more than 100 letters from enthusiastic 
viewers foster said and theres not a single one that says 
this is communist propaganda 
turning vremya into us tv fare makes for a fast day at 
international video broadcasts the virginiabased company that 
captures the early vremya from a soviet satellite each day at 
430 am est 
the signal is altered to us broadcast standards and two ivb 
translators soviet emigres trained at toprated soviet language 
institutes translate the videotape 
we have from 730 am to 115 pm to get it all translated 
edited and dubbed said dick kuiper who is in charge of the 
production he recalled one day last week when they finished with 
just a minute to spare 
television has been mikhail gorbachevs ally in perestroika the 
restructuring of soviet society kuiper said 
i think he specifically chose that medium as a powerful tool 
to get his message to society past all the editors and middle 
managers he said 
the vremya experiment already is a qualified success foster 
said i think it will be a success even if it proves that the 
show may be a good product without a market he added 
so far he said theres been no word from the underwriters 
corporations and foundations that ultimately would bear most of the 
programs cost but wgbh is moving to extend the vremya test 
for two more weeks 
</TEXT>
