the soviet legislature on tuesday urged a 
crackdown on illegal demonstrations scheduled for sunday and said 
authorities should exercise tight control on legal rallies the 
tass news agency reported 
the legislators saying they feared that extremists and criminal 
elements will exploit the demonstrations to destabilize the 
political situation adopted a resolution urging law enforcement 
agencies to take special measures to keep demonstrators in line 
the rallies were organized by various political groups in 
moscow leningrad and other major cities to express their 
attitude to changes taking place in the country tass said 
as far as newspaper reports indicate forces interested in 
destabilizing the situation also intend to join the 
demonstrators the news agency said 
the resolution introduced in the supreme soviet legislature by 
deputy nikolai pivovarov said unsanctioned rallies should be 
curbed and legal demonstrations be held in specifically assigned 
places 
in order to prevent actions by militants and possibly 
criminal forces the supreme soviet has asked the government and 
local authorities to adopt all necessary measures to protect law 
and order tass said 
the news agency quoted several deputies as saying there had been 
an increase in demonstrations under the perestroika reforms of 
president mikhail s gorbachev and that many of them had taken on 
an antistate character with some demonstrators exhorting people 
to violence 
