at barraca garrison bengo province near luanda 
there was no independent confirmation of the claims but the 
angolan state news agency said 10 rebels died in clashes in central 
huambo cuanza south and benguela provinces last week 
the battle for mavinga said to be the heaviest in the 15year 
conflict has darkened hopes of getting government and rebel 
representatives back to the negotiating table 
peace talks collapsed only weeks after savimbi and president 
jose eduardo dos santos sealed a truce before 18 african leaders at 
gbadolite zaire on june 22 
the rebels have sabotaged power and water supplies to luanda 
several times in the past month 
unita has been fighting to force the government to share power 
since shortly after angola gained independence from portugal in 
1975 
