record of 572 billion in 1988 
that is the money left for farmers after deducting cash expenses 
from gross cash income in a calendar year it can include proceeds 
from sales of commodities held over from previous years 
net farm income another method of bookkeeping may be in the 
range of 44 billion to 49 billion this year compared with 48 
billion in 1989 and 427 billion in 1988 
this method measures income from farming during a specific year 
