system and it has other features i think are worthy of very 
serious consideration foley said 
workers pay a 765 percent social security payroll tax an 
amount that is in addition to their income tax employers must also 
pay the government an equal amount on behalf of each employee 
critics have charged that the payroll tax discriminates against 
low and middleincome workers because it is levied only on the 
first 51300 of annual earnings people pay no payroll tax on 
