leaders of the church of england were urged on 
tuesday to reject an unpublished report that recommends homosexuals 
be treated with more sympathy by the church 
the report was commissioned by the bishops in the churchs 
policymaking general synod who wanted advice on dealing with 
matters of homosexuality but they decided not to publish it 
