synods regular february session that leaked copies of the report 
indicated it contradicted a 1987 synod decision that homosexual 
acts fell short of the christian ideal 
he said the leaked version appeared to suggest that only 
onethird of the bishops held to the biblical and traditional view 
of the church which opposes homosexual relationships 
while most bishops in the words of the report would not 
sponsor or ordain anyone whom they knew to be homosexually active 
