<TEXT>
west german chancellor helmut kohl 
told a rally of 90000 cheering east germans tuesday that his 
government will provide massive aid to help the troubled countrys 
social safety net 
west german politicians who themselves face the voters in 
december are increasingly using east germanys election campaign 
to promote their own causes 
with plans for reunification moving quickly west german 
politicians are also trying to enlist supporters in east germany 
for future elections 
the west germans also are lending campaign support to their 
inexperienced sister parties in east germany and allied groups that 
have sprung up since the peaceful prodemocracy revolution in 
october and the ouster of the hardline communist government 
the countrys first free elections are on march 18 
kohl a christian democrat was lending support to east 
germanys conservatives he was repeatedly cheered by the large 
crowd waving west german flags and calling for quick unification 
the rally was organized by the socalled alliance for 
germany a group comprising the east german christian democrats 
the german social union and democratic awakening 
the christian democrats are trying to shake off 40 years of past 
association with the communists 
kohl took a swipe at the opposition social democrats and their 
veteran leader willy brandt saying brandt only one year ago 
dismissed german unity as unrealistic 
east german social democrats are widely predicted to win the 
march election brandt remains hugely popular in east germany and 
has often spokesn at rallies there east german social democrats 
have said they will make brandt their honorary chairman as well 
addressing fears about the planned introduction of the west 
german mark as east germanys currency kohl said his government 
will help east germany develop a similar comprehensive social 
security network that is enjoyed by west germans 
east germans have expressed fears that the switch to west 
germanys mighty mark will wipe out their savings erode the value 
of pensions and trigger massive umemployment as the transition to 
capitalism forces unprofitable enterprises to close 
but kohl said his government will take care of the jobless 
pensioners and others who might be affected by the switch in 
currency 
kohl tried to justify his refusal to give massive aid to the 
current interim communistled government 
i was not ready to invest billions in a system if i cant see 
that the citizens will benefit kohl said 
the crowd responded by shouting helmut helmut 
lothar de maiziere the christian democrat leader received loud 
cheers when he said german unity will come because the people 
want it 
