<DOCNO> AP900220-0195 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
a powerful symbol of the beauty and grandeur of 
france the champs elysees has been celebrated in song fiction and 
on the silver screen by generations of international talent 
who could forget the sweet innocence of american actress jean 
seberg hawking the paris herald tribune on the champs elysees in 
jeanluc godards 1959 movie classic breathless costarring 
the young jeanpaul belmondo 
french audiences still wince as german tanks roll down the 
champs elysees in is paris burning 1965 rene clements epic 
about the efforts of a german general to save the french capital 
from destruction as ordered by nazi leader adolph hitler 
dozens of writers lived on or near the treeshaded avenue 
marcel proust used to play in the gardens at the rond point where 
he met the young woman who would later inspire his two most 
mememorable female characters gilberte and odette of remembrance 
of things past 
gustave flaubert was fascinated with the champs elysees and the 
role it played in the social lives of fashionable parisians in the 
novel the sentimental education frederic makes frequent 
pilgrimages there to catch a glimpse of his beloved madame arnoux 
victor hugo took up residence on the champs elysees after being 
evicted from his left bank home he remained there until 1832 when 
fighting broke out under his windows confining the entire family 
to the house for days soon after he moved to a safer home on 
the place des vosges 
british novelist charles dickens seeking the anonymity of a 
foreign capital chose paris and a home on the champs elysees but 
after the publication of martin chuzzlewit and its enormous 
success he was recognized even by the french and finally agreed 
to give weekly public readings of the book in english 
honore de balzacs the human comedy contains 41 references 
to the champs elysees in his classic father goriot the champs 
is where the miserly old man wanders secretly admiring handsome 
young ladies in horsedrawn carriages 
stendhal summed up the champs of old im going to look for 
the peace and quiet of the country in the only place where it 
exists in france on a fourth floor overlooking the champs 
elysees 
joe dassins hit tune of the 1960s summed up the story of the 
champs today in sun and rain at noon or midnight you can get 
anything you want on the champs elysees 
</TEXT>
