william usery who helped forge the tentative settlement announced 
jan 1 
trumka called miners in castlewood va at about 915 am to 
tell them the strike was officially over kirkland and mrs dole 
joined in the call 
kirkland called the vote a happy conclusion to a long and very 
gallant struggle 
he told the miners your example and your steadfastness and 
your solidarity has been an inspiration to the entire trade union 
movement not just here but throughout the world its given us all 
