question their involvement with tobacco companies he said he hoped 
to see them step forward to renounce tobacco ads and join in our 
antismoking efforts 
sullivan said the annual percapita costs of smokingrelated 
disease was 221 nationally he said that ranges from a low of 56 
a person in utah to 284 in rhode island 
the cost comes out of the pockets of smokers and nonsmokers 
alike mostly in the forms of increased health care and insurance 
costs sullivan said 
sullivan recently condemned rj reynolds tobacco co for its 
plans to market a cigarette targeted at blacks reynolds 
subsequently dropped those plans but it now intends to testmarket 
a cigarette called dakota that news accounts said under one 
proposal would be geared toward young women with a high school 
education or less 
sullivan has been concerned about minorities because they have 
higher rates of smoking than whites and they have a higher rate of 
smokingrelated disease and death 
smoking causes about 390000 deaths in the united states and 
about 29 percent of adults smoke according to government 
statistics 
