freeportmcmoran gold co which operates two 
gold mining operations in nevada has agreed to be bought by 
minorco sa for about 705 million officials said tuesday 
minorco a europeanbased natural resources group with principal 
interests in mining and processing metals will commence a tender 
offer of 17 per share for freeportmcmoran gold which is 61 
percent owned by freeportmcmoran inc of new orleans the deal 
was approved by the freeportmcmoran gold board the companies said 
minorco failed last year in a 62 billion bid to take over 
consolidated gold fields plc gold fields was later bought by 
hanson plc in a friendly 57 billion deal 
the purchase of freeportmcmoran gold is a major step in 
minorcos strategy of becoming an operator rather than a passive 
investor said hank slack an executive of minorco 
investors greeted the deal enthusiastically freeportmoran gold 
stock rose 262 to 1662 a share on the new york stock exchange 
tuesday 
freeportmcmoran inc said it agreed to tender its 61 percent 
interest into the offer or to sell those shares to minorco 
separately if the tender offer is not completed 
freeportmcmoran gold has joint venture interest in two nevada 
gold mining operations the company owns 70 percent of the jerritt 
canyon operation and 60 percent of the big springs operation and 
operates both mines 
attributable gold production at the two sites in 1989 was 
244100 ounces of gold at a cash cost of 207 per ounce 
for the year ending dec 31 1989 freeportmcmoran gold revenue 
was 879 million and the company had total assets of 1792 
million 
freeportmcmoran inc said it would use the proceeds of the sale 
to help finance development of a sulfur discovery in the gulf of 
mexico and a coppergold discovery in indonesia said company 
spokesman craig e saporito 
we announced our intention of selling some assets and reducing 
our debts by 12 billion to 15 billion and using the money to 
develop those discoveries this made sense it was not part of our 
core assets and not part of our longrange plans saporito said 
as of dec 31 1989 freeportmcmoran gold had proven and 
probable reserves of 222 million recoverable ounces of gold at its 
two mining operations the majority of it at jerritt canyon 
