legal dispute 
under the agreement mccaw will manage the milwaukee joint 
venture and own a 92 percent stake in it with graphic owning 8 
percent 
mccaw also agreed to transfer to graphic its rights to cellular 
telephone interests around indianapolis ind 
the settlement is subject to federal and state regulatory 
approval 
mccaw based in kirkland wash is the nations largest 
cellular telephone company with customers in 127 markets in 26 
states 
graphic based in englewood operates one of the countrys 
largest radio paging businesses is a major provider of cellular 
radio telephone services and serves telecommunications customers in 
the united states and the united kingdom 
mccaw had sued graphic claiming the new jersey company breached 
an oral agreement made several years ago in which it pledged to 
sell its share of the milwaukee market for 40 per potential 
customer or about 30 million far below todays estimated market 
value of 175 million 
graphic denied agreeing to sell at that price 
under a settlement reached last week in us district court in 
washington state mccaw and graphic agreed to create a regional 
joint venture by combining graphics interest in milwaukee with 
mccaws cellular interests in wisconsin and rockford ill the new 
business would have a potential market of more than 1 million 
customers 
