<TEXT>
zenith electronics corp on tuesday revealed a 
disagreement with groupe bull over the final sale price of zeniths 
computer business to the french concern 
both parties agreed the issue does not threaten to derail bulls 
acquisition of zenith data systems which was effectively completed 
in december 
but because the eventual outcome will affect zeniths financial 
condition the company reported fourthquarter and annual results 
only for its consumer electronics business which consists mainly 
of televisions and tv components 
the results included a 47 percent drop in fourthquarter profit 
and a 17 million loss for all of 1989 which the company said 
reflected higher material and labor costs despite higher sales 
volume and efficiency improvements 
zenith is disputing bulls request for a 49 million refund on 
its dec 28 payment of 4964 million for zenith data systems said 
zenith spokesman john i taylor 
zenith had previously indicated that it expected a further 
payment not a refund request from bull as the final adjustment to 
the purchase price 
clearly we have a difference of opinion of significant 
magnitude zenith chairman jerry k pearlman said in a statement 
zenith characterized the disagreement as a major dispute and 
said bull may have violated the terms of their contract 
a bull spokesman denied the charge and downplayed the issue 
pointing out that zenith has 30 days to review the request and 
another 30 days in which to negotiate a resolution before an 
arbitrator steps in 
we dont see it as major dispute at all said spokesman 
patrick marx in a telephone interview from bulls paris 
headquarters 
zenith announced oct 2 an agreement to sell the computer unit 
to bull for 919 million plus the adjusted net book value of the 
assets sold for a total that zenith initially estimated at 635 
million and later lowered to an estimated 610 million 
on dec 28 bull paid zenith 4964 million in cash an 
agreedupon amount that taylor said reflected 90 percent of the sum 
of the 919 million premium and the adjusted net book value of the 
computer units assets through nov 30 
the payment effectively closed the sale of zenith data systems 
leaving only a final adjustment that would include the units asset 
value at the end of december 
the sale agreement provided for bull to submit the final 
adjustment based on an audit of zenith data systems commissioned 
by bull 
electronics analysts said the dispute was a surprise and that a 
49 million refund would hurt zenith 
if it works against them it will affect their ability to 
bring down debt levels said laura lederman an analyst with duff 
amp phelps inc in chicago 
zenith had previously estimated a 22 million fourthquarter 
operating profit from the computer unit but said tuesday that 
because of substantial deterioration in the business during 
december it expects the division to report a net loss 
for its consumer electronics business zenith reported net 
income of 4 million or 15 cents per common share for the three 
months ending dec 31 compared with 75 million or 29 cents per 
share for the same period a year ago 
fourthquarter revenue from consumer electronics rose slightly 
to 443 million from 440 million in 1988 
for the full year zenith reported a net loss from consumer 
electronics of of 17 million or 64 cents a share compared with a 
net loss of 11 million or 42 cents a share in 1988 
annual revenue from consumer electronics rose 11 percent to 15 
billion from 14 billion in 1988 
