<TEXT>
chevron corp said tuesday it was cutting 
its us oil exploration and production business because of 
diminishing oil reserves in the continental united states and 
public opposition to offshore drilling 
chevron usa the domestic oil and gas subsidiary of the 
nations thirdlargest oil company said it expects to eliminate 
800 to 1000 positions or 10 to 12 percent of the organization 
including middle and senior managers 
chevron which will expand its international exploration and 
production plans to accelerate sales of us assets by unloading 
about 1000 of its 1700 domestic oil fields for some 700 million 
over the next two years 
the company said it will sell the fields which account for only 
11 percent of current production to small or regional operators 
for whom the fields might make a better fit or negotiate trades 
with large companies 
the changes are expected to result in a charge against 1990 
firstquarter earnings of between 25 million and 30 million the 
company said 
chevron with 345 billion in assets took a 12 billion 
charge against fourthquarter 1989 earnings primarily because of an 
inactive oil field and environmental cleanup costs the charge led 
to an 883 million loss for the quarter and depressed 1989 profits 
to 251 million from 177 billion in 1988 
chevrons problems left its stock undervalued according to 
analysts and vulnerable to a takeover or restructuring 
that in turn spurred heavy trading in recent months while 
chevron engaged in a legal battle to force pennzoil co to sell its 
88 percent share of chevron stock chevron said it is worried that 
pennzoil would try to use its position to force a restructuring 
detrimental to chevron stockholders 
wall street reacted with mild enthusiasm to tuesdays 
announcement as chevrons stock down 112 before the release hit 
the wire late in the trading day rebounded slightly to close down 
67 cents at 6925 
im very encouraged said frederick leuffer an analyst with 
cj lawrence morgan grenfell inc in new york i think it 
represents a turn for the company all the details are not out 
this is only a relatively modest step in the right direction we 
should find out more tomorrow 
chevron executives scheduled a meeting with analysts wednesday 
in new york 
the company said its restructuring is aimed mostly at cutting 
layers of management and lowering operating costs to make it more 
competitive and enhance profitability and shareholders investments 
leuffer said chevron the nations third largest oil company 
after exxon corp and mobil oil corp is vastly undervalued he 
placed its value at at least 116 a share and said the stock 
could reach 90 a share 
in 1988 and 1989 chevron sold about 210 million worth of 
domestic assets 
the company said it hoped that many staff cuts could be achieved 
voluntarily 
the organizational changes include 
chevron usas three current exploration land and 
production regions based in san ramon calif houston and new 
orleans will be eliminated including their management 
organization structure and positions 
in place of the regional organization the exploration and 
production functions will be divided into seven distinct business 
units each directly responsible for its own financial performance 
plus a centralized land department all will report to a chevron 
usa senior vice president in san francisco 
in production five business units will be set up headquartered 
in bakersfield calif denver midland and houston texas and new 
orleans current production activities now managed from ventura 
calif will be consolidated and report to the bakersfield office 
</TEXT>
