used his position as an operations manager to transfer shares from 
a prudentialbache mutual fund account to a fictitious account 
kofler said he wrote letters in the name of the fictitious 
account holder asking that the shares be redeemed and sent to one 
or more private post office boxes 
keenan told kofler he was imposing the lenient sentence 
primarily at the request of the us attorneys office but he 
warned kofler that any similar future conduct would result in a 
jail term 
lawrence said he did not know if kofler still works in the 
securities industry and declined to comment on why his office 
sought leniency 
</TEXT>
