cathay pacific airways has exercised an option to 
purchase four boeing 747400s for about 550 million boeing 
commercial airplane group confirmed 
the order brings to 14 the number of longrange 747400s the 
hong kongbased carrier has committed to buy the airline also has 
ordered 15 other 747s of other series six 747300s eight 747200 
passenger jets and one 200 freighter 
cathay has taken delivery of three 747400s from boeing it uses 
them to fly passengers nonstop between hong kong and european 
destinations 
turnedup wingtips a 12foot longer wingspan and the use of 
advanced composite materials help make boeings new 747400 
jetliner the longestrange passenger jet in the world it can fly 
8400 statute miles nonstop fully loaded 
tuesdays order brings total boeing 747400 orders to 259 
so far this year boeing has announced orders for 88 aircraft 
valued at about 728 billion 
